WEBVTT

00:01.335 --> 00:03.303
Tonight, Emma Grede,
founder and CEO of

00:03.403 --> 00:05.305
smash-hit apparel brand
Good American

00:05.405 --> 00:08.408
and founding partner of SKIMS,
returns to the Tank.

00:08.509 --> 00:11.578
God, you are speaking
my language 100%.

00:11.678 --> 00:13.180
We want to service
an audience

00:13.280 --> 00:15.282
that has been overlooked
for years.

00:15.382 --> 00:16.683
You're allowed
to make a...

00:16.783 --> 00:19.219
Mess! Mess! Mess!

00:19.319 --> 00:22.322
The Plufl allow you to turn
any place into a napping space.

00:22.422 --> 00:24.691
I was awarded one of
Oprah's Favorite Things.

00:24.791 --> 00:25.893
Are you
making any money?

00:25.993 --> 00:27.394
No, I have lost
a fortune this year.

00:27.494 --> 00:28.462
We have sales of
$2 million.

00:28.562 --> 00:29.496
$2 million?

00:29.596 --> 00:30.597
$2 million.

00:30.697 --> 00:31.965
We put it on TikTok,
and it went viral.

00:32.065 --> 00:34.001
I just don't get it.
Why are people buying these?

00:34.101 --> 00:35.235
Why not?
Oh, I like it.

00:35.335 --> 00:36.503
Please!

00:36.603 --> 00:39.640
It broke my heart, what you
did. I wept like a baby.

00:45.178 --> 00:46.346
Let's go, team!

00:46.446 --> 00:49.116
We're energetic. We're fun.
This is our moment.

00:49.216 --> 00:50.217
Let's go!

00:50.317 --> 00:53.954
Let's go. Let's do it.
I'm so excited.

00:54.054 --> 00:55.355
First in the Tank

00:55.455 --> 00:59.092
is a way to get just as cozy
as the world's best nappers.

01:07.401 --> 01:09.136
Hi, Sharks.
My name is Noah.

01:09.236 --> 01:10.604
And my name is Yuki.

01:10.704 --> 01:13.574
We're recent college grads,
and we're here seeking
$200,000

01:13.674 --> 01:16.043
in exchange for
10% of our company, Plufl.

01:16.143 --> 01:18.812
Sharks, we all have
those long days

01:18.912 --> 01:20.280
when we crave
a cozy nap

01:20.380 --> 01:22.716
to get away from
the troubles of the world.

01:22.816 --> 01:25.052
When you just need a break
from the stress and exhaustion,

01:25.152 --> 01:27.287
you could quite literally
sleep anywhere.

01:27.387 --> 01:29.690
I mean, look at our buddy
Kipper over here.

01:29.790 --> 01:31.992
Sharks, don't you find
yourself jealous of Kipper?

01:32.092 --> 01:34.294
Able to nap literally
wherever he wants.

01:34.394 --> 01:37.030
Don't you ever wish you
could have what Kipper has?

01:37.130 --> 01:38.365
Well, now you can.

01:38.465 --> 01:41.134
Introducing...

01:41.234 --> 01:42.169
Plufl!

01:42.269 --> 01:44.571
It's a dog bed for humans!

01:44.671 --> 01:46.740
That's right, Sharks.
I didn't see
that coming.

01:46.840 --> 01:48.041
Plufl is the world's
first dog bed

01:48.141 --> 01:49.810
specifically designed
for humans.

01:49.910 --> 01:54.348
Because if you work like a
dog, why not sleep like one?

01:54.448 --> 01:55.682
When you sink into
the Plufl,

01:55.782 --> 01:58.118
you're surrounded by the
softest materials and textures.

01:58.218 --> 01:59.786
The soft pillow border
allows you to

01:59.886 --> 02:01.154
tuck your hands
and feet inside

02:01.254 --> 02:05.425
and maximize what we like
to call "the snuggle factor"!

02:05.525 --> 02:06.493
The plush faux fur

02:06.593 --> 02:08.629
and high-grade
orthopedic memory foam

02:08.729 --> 02:11.398
allow you to turn any place
into a napping space.

02:12.866 --> 02:16.603
Doesn't he look cozy?
I wouldn't want to wake him up.

02:16.703 --> 02:18.905
Sharks, we want to bring
this revolutionary

02:19.006 --> 02:20.674
napping experience everywhere.

02:20.774 --> 02:22.209
So don't sleep
on this opportunity

02:22.309 --> 02:26.046
to join us in building
a napping empire.

02:26.146 --> 02:28.782
Alright, so who wants
to try out the Plufl?

02:28.882 --> 02:29.883
I do.
I'll do it.

02:29.983 --> 02:31.585
Yeah,
I want to touch it.

02:31.685 --> 02:33.153
Robert, we figured you would
really want to try it out.

02:33.253 --> 02:34.621
I definitely want
to try it!

02:34.721 --> 02:36.657
Come on, anyone,
give it a go.

02:36.757 --> 02:38.191
Alright.

02:38.291 --> 02:39.726
You're such a Robert. Ohh.

02:39.826 --> 02:40.927
Robert,
would you like a blanket?

02:41.028 --> 02:42.229
Yes, I would
like a blanket.

02:42.329 --> 02:43.430
Mark, here,
lay in this one.

02:43.530 --> 02:44.598
Ahh.

02:44.698 --> 02:45.932
Robert,
try curling up a little bit,

02:46.033 --> 02:47.634
like a little baby.

02:47.734 --> 02:50.237
Shockingly,
it's really comfortable.

02:50.337 --> 02:51.271
Mark,
give it a go.

02:51.371 --> 02:53.306
Ohh.
I wanna see
if I can fit.

02:53.407 --> 02:55.342
Pull right up.
You can put your legs out.

02:55.442 --> 02:56.677
Yeah, kind of lean
your arms on it.

02:56.777 --> 02:58.278
Kind of relax.
Lounge a little bit, yeah.

02:58.378 --> 03:00.147
It's actually not bad.

03:00.247 --> 03:01.248
It's not bad.

03:01.348 --> 03:02.716
Oh, yeah, Robert.

03:03.850 --> 03:05.318
Wow.
How much is it?

03:05.419 --> 03:07.854
It's $399. We're currently
taking pre-orders at $399.

03:07.954 --> 03:09.256
$399?

03:09.356 --> 03:11.224
Yeah, $399.
Oh. Okay.

03:11.324 --> 03:12.426
What does
it cost you to make?

03:12.526 --> 03:14.361
Our landed cost
is $140.

03:14.461 --> 03:15.762
Oh, wow.

03:15.862 --> 03:17.364
And you <i>must</i> have sales.

03:17.464 --> 03:18.532
Yes, we do.

03:18.632 --> 03:20.100
Three months ago,
we launched on Kickstarter.

03:20.200 --> 03:23.470
Our initial goal was $25,000.
We blew it out of the water.

03:23.570 --> 03:25.972
We had $280,000
in 30 days. Wow.

03:26.073 --> 03:28.775
And we've done over $130,000
in sales since.

03:28.875 --> 03:30.444
And how much of that
have you delivered?

03:30.544 --> 03:32.546
We've just started
the manufacturing process.

03:32.646 --> 03:35.048
With that being none.

03:35.148 --> 03:36.583
So, throughout
our prototyping process,

03:36.683 --> 03:39.419
we've tested our versions with
about 50 different beta testers,

03:39.519 --> 03:40.954
and they all
absolutely loved it.

03:41.054 --> 03:42.856
Well, I'm curious--
Did you used to lay in,

03:42.956 --> 03:45.792
like, a really big, oversize
dog bed or something?

03:45.892 --> 03:47.294
Yeah, so, throughout
my time at school,

03:47.394 --> 03:49.963
I worked as a barista
at a local college coffee shop

03:50.063 --> 03:51.264
where there lived
a Great Dane. Oh.

03:51.364 --> 03:52.466
And so, one day,

03:52.566 --> 03:55.135
during a long shift,
I was looking at this dog

03:55.235 --> 03:57.204
napping really comfortably
in its bed,

03:57.304 --> 03:58.872
and I found myself
kind of jealous.

03:58.972 --> 04:02.142
Like, "Man, why can't
that be me right now?"

04:02.242 --> 04:03.744
And then I had
an idea--

04:03.844 --> 04:05.112
dog beds for humans.

04:05.212 --> 04:06.213
Ta-da!

04:06.313 --> 04:08.014
I was all over Google,
trying to see

04:08.115 --> 04:11.084
if a product like this
existed, but I found nothing.

04:11.184 --> 04:12.853
So I was calling up Yuki,
a good friend,

04:12.953 --> 04:15.255
telling him about the concept,
and he loved it.

04:15.355 --> 04:17.224
So we partnered with
a local designer in Vancouver

04:17.324 --> 04:19.025
to build
our first prototype,

04:19.126 --> 04:21.328
and it turned out so awesome
that we had people

04:21.428 --> 04:23.797
lined up all over our campus
just to try it out.

04:23.897 --> 04:24.965
I-- I just don't get it.

04:25.065 --> 04:26.833
Like, why are people
buying these?

04:26.933 --> 04:28.535
Like, what--
Who's your customer?

04:28.635 --> 04:29.636
Why not?
Why do you need it?

04:29.736 --> 04:30.570
Oh, I like it.
I like it.

04:30.670 --> 04:31.638
Really?
I don't get it.

04:31.738 --> 04:33.540
Your kids-- Oh, come on.
Your kids?

04:33.640 --> 04:35.008
My 8-year-old would
probably love it. Yes.

04:35.108 --> 04:37.010
But, like, do I want
a dog bed in my living room?

04:37.110 --> 04:38.245
Yes!

04:38.345 --> 04:40.247
So we started out just
creating a fun product

04:40.347 --> 04:42.282
that would bring joy and
comfort to people's lives,

04:42.382 --> 04:44.985
but we realized we're building
something bigger than that

04:45.085 --> 04:47.554
when we put it on TikTok
and it went viral,

04:47.654 --> 04:49.790
and we started getting flooded
with messages from people

04:49.890 --> 04:52.125
sharing just how excited
they were for this product.

04:52.225 --> 04:54.661
We spoke with mothers
of children with sensory issues,

04:54.761 --> 04:56.396
veterans with
physical trauma...
Oh, yeah.

04:56.496 --> 04:58.598
...people that suffer
from a range of sleep issues

04:58.698 --> 04:59.666
that just need a more
comfortable place to rest.

04:59.766 --> 05:01.668
But you've never
delivered these.

05:01.768 --> 05:03.303
It's only been three months
since we graduated.

05:03.403 --> 05:05.172
When do you anticipate
being able to deliver?

05:05.272 --> 05:07.941
Because you've got
no real customers at the moment,

05:08.041 --> 05:09.543
which means you've got
no real reviews.

05:09.643 --> 05:11.812
Like, that, to me,
is just a big red flag.

05:11.912 --> 05:13.880
Yeah, we expect to deliver
around late November

05:13.980 --> 05:14.881
to early December.

05:14.981 --> 05:16.683
And when did you
take the orders?

05:16.783 --> 05:19.753
We took orders back
starting from April.

05:19.853 --> 05:21.354
I mean, that's some
pre-order period.

05:21.454 --> 05:23.023
We're talking, what,
seven months?

05:23.123 --> 05:24.224
- That's right. Yeah.
- Mm-hmm.

05:24.324 --> 05:26.626
Why has it taken you so long
to get them delivered?

05:26.726 --> 05:29.162
That's a long time
for just 1,200 units. Exactly.

05:29.262 --> 05:31.531
Well, but you have to have
your production time, right?

05:31.631 --> 05:33.567
I mean, I don't know how long
it takes to make one of these.

05:33.667 --> 05:35.468
How long does it
take to make one?

05:35.569 --> 05:39.139
Yeah, so the 1,200 units
takes about 2 months to make
and 2 months to ship out.

05:39.239 --> 05:41.408
So we're looking at ways
to reduce our lead time,

05:41.508 --> 05:42.709
but this is
our first go at it.

05:42.809 --> 05:44.644
Okay, guys, look,
I think it's a crazy idea.

05:44.744 --> 05:45.846
That's why I like it.

05:45.946 --> 05:48.148
However,
you are unproven, untested.

05:48.248 --> 05:50.951
There's $200,000 for 10%,
imputes to $2 million.

05:51.084 --> 05:52.619
It's not worth
$2 million right now,

05:52.719 --> 05:58.191
so I'll do it for $200,000
cash-a-roni for 30%.

05:59.860 --> 06:01.595
Wow, that's way better
than I thought.

06:01.695 --> 06:03.230
You know, out of him,
that's not so bad.

06:03.330 --> 06:04.831
Mark,
remember our Hug Sleep?

06:04.931 --> 06:06.333
Yeah. Yeah.
It's killing it.

06:06.433 --> 06:08.368
So, like, Mark and I
did a deal with Hug Sleep.
Yeah, yeah.

06:08.468 --> 06:10.136
It was almost like
a sleeping bag, but not.

06:10.237 --> 06:11.071
Yeah, mm-hmm.

06:11.171 --> 06:12.439
Stretchy fabric
that wraps--

06:12.539 --> 06:14.207
I literally use it
every night.

06:14.307 --> 06:15.308
I know you do.

06:15.408 --> 06:17.344
I sleep so much better
in my Hug Sleep.

06:17.444 --> 06:18.979
Yes, it makes you
sleep better.

06:19.079 --> 06:21.047
Yeah. It's like being swaddled
as an adult.
And we know.

06:21.147 --> 06:24.117
We know. We're at $15 million
in sales in two years.

06:24.217 --> 06:26.052
I mean, we love-- Hug Sleep's
a huge inspiration for us,

06:26.152 --> 06:27.587
and a lot of their
kind of story about

06:27.687 --> 06:30.123
helping people with anxiety
just find more comfort.

06:30.223 --> 06:31.558
Without question, yeah.
Without question.

06:31.658 --> 06:33.526
Their messaging about, like,
why don't adults need hugs, too?

06:33.627 --> 06:34.794
That's kind of what
we're trying to embrace here.

06:34.895 --> 06:37.063
Like, adults need comfort.
They need to be cozy.

06:37.163 --> 06:39.032
So, Lori, are you saying
we should work together on
this? So, guys,
can anyone knock you off?

06:39.132 --> 06:41.167
Do you have a patent?
Is there any kind of
protection?

06:41.268 --> 06:45.038
So, right now, we're the first
to market with this product.

06:45.138 --> 06:46.673
We filed for
our provisional patent,

06:46.773 --> 06:49.109
and are currently working
on utility and design patents.

06:49.209 --> 06:51.177
We've also filed for
the trademark for our name

06:51.278 --> 06:54.014
as well as for the phrase
"the dog bed for humans."

06:54.114 --> 06:55.548
Yeah, I don't, I--

06:55.649 --> 06:58.785
It's a dog bed for humans.

06:58.885 --> 07:00.253
I don't see it.
It's not for me. I'm out.

07:00.353 --> 07:03.023
Thank you, Robert.
We appreciate the feedback.

07:03.123 --> 07:04.691
One thing we just want
to touch on is that

07:04.791 --> 07:06.993
this is more than just
a large dog bed.

07:07.093 --> 07:08.595
We actually changed
a lot of the components.

07:08.695 --> 07:11.231
For one thing, we swapped out
the conventional pillow base

07:11.331 --> 07:13.533
for more supportive orthopedic
and memory foam pads

07:13.633 --> 07:14.868
so people can actually
feel supported.

07:14.968 --> 07:16.569
It's a dog bed
for humans.

07:16.670 --> 07:19.039
Listen, I'm going to just,
like, get out of the way here.

07:19.139 --> 07:21.374
But I just--
I do not understand it.

07:21.474 --> 07:24.811
Like, I don't understand
who is buying this product,

07:24.911 --> 07:26.579
and so I'm out.

07:26.680 --> 07:28.615
Yeah.
Thank you for the feedback.
O'Leary: A little bit of
skepticism here.

07:28.715 --> 07:29.849
Guys, we want to--
we want to make an offer.

07:29.950 --> 07:32.619
We think it's a great
complement to Hug Sleep,

07:32.719 --> 07:35.622
so there's all kinds of ways
we can help sell it.

07:35.722 --> 07:37.624
So, we'd like to make you
the offer of the $200,000

07:37.724 --> 07:38.992
you asked for,
for 20%.

07:39.092 --> 07:40.694
The two of us together.
The two of us together.

07:40.794 --> 07:41.695
Um...

07:41.795 --> 07:43.129
Thank you
for that offer.

07:43.229 --> 07:44.597
Noah and I will take
a little bit of time

07:44.698 --> 07:46.466
just to
talk about it.

07:46.566 --> 07:48.335
Seriously, there's something
to talk about?

07:48.435 --> 07:51.871
Would you guys be open
to $200,000 for 15%?

07:51.972 --> 07:54.207
No.
No.

07:54.307 --> 07:55.542
It's a dog bed!

07:55.642 --> 07:58.345
It's got to be enough in there
for both of us to get excited.

07:58.445 --> 07:59.646
And we have experience
with this.

07:59.746 --> 08:00.880
Kevin, do you want
to change your offer?

08:00.981 --> 08:01.915
Alright,
we've got a deal.

08:04.217 --> 08:06.553
Kevin, it just went away from
you, just like that.

08:06.653 --> 08:08.855
Okay, $200,000 for 40%.

08:11.358 --> 08:14.227
- Congratulations.
- Thank you so much.

08:14.327 --> 08:15.295
- Yeah.
- Thank you.

08:15.395 --> 08:16.363
- Great stuff, guys.
- Thank you, guys.

08:16.463 --> 08:17.664
Thank you so much, guys.

08:17.764 --> 08:18.732
Well done, guys.

08:18.832 --> 08:21.134
It's a dog bed
for humans!

08:21.234 --> 08:23.770
Exactly. Exactly.

08:23.870 --> 08:24.738
What are you gonna
do with that?

08:24.838 --> 08:25.839
I'm gonna take a nap.

08:25.939 --> 08:26.973
We're in
the sleep business.

08:28.975 --> 08:31.177
Noah and I just graduated
about three months ago,

08:31.277 --> 08:34.047
and the fact that we're here
right now on "Shark Tank"

08:34.147 --> 08:36.383
and got a deal from
Mark and Lori?
Yeah.

08:36.483 --> 08:38.985
It's-- It's crazy.
I really can't believe it.

08:39.085 --> 08:40.387
And that's a testament
to the fact

08:40.487 --> 08:42.222
that if anyone cares
about something

08:42.322 --> 08:45.291
and dedicates their time
and effort, they can do it.

08:58.538 --> 08:59.439
Mwah.

09:04.210 --> 09:06.679
Next up is a company
who wants to make everyone

09:06.780 --> 09:09.716
in the wedding party
feel as pretty as the bride.

09:17.624 --> 09:20.560
Hi, I'm Ashley.
And I'm Charles.

09:20.660 --> 09:22.062
We're from
Washington, D. C.,

09:22.162 --> 09:26.699
and we're seeking $250,000
for 10% equity in our company,

09:26.800 --> 09:29.536
Bridal Babes,
the first bridal fashion company

09:29.636 --> 09:32.872
for multi-cultural women
and women with curves.

09:32.972 --> 09:35.375
We are changing
the bridal fashion game

09:35.475 --> 09:39.679
with curve-hugging and
attractive bridesmaid dresses.

09:39.779 --> 09:44.017
Yes, they do exist,
and I'm wearing one today.

09:44.117 --> 09:45.018
Whoo!

09:45.118 --> 09:46.152
When we were
getting married,

09:46.252 --> 09:48.721
I remember Ashley mentioning
how difficult it was

09:48.822 --> 09:51.057
to find the perfect dresses
for bridesmaids.

09:51.157 --> 09:53.426
My bridesmaids
dress shopping experience

09:53.526 --> 09:56.396
at traditional bridal shops
was horrible.

09:56.496 --> 09:59.199
I ended up searching
the Internet high and low,

09:59.299 --> 10:01.501
and finally found something
that would work,

10:01.601 --> 10:04.971
and when my girls put it on,
they instantly fell in love.

10:05.071 --> 10:07.307
And the wedding went viral
because no one had ever seen

10:07.407 --> 10:09.976
bridesmaids in such
stunning looks before.

10:10.076 --> 10:11.778
That's when we knew
that we were on to something.

10:11.878 --> 10:13.947
We went from
high school sweethearts

10:14.047 --> 10:17.417
to newlyweds and
business partners overnight.

10:17.517 --> 10:18.618
Aww.

10:18.718 --> 10:21.354
Bridal Babes offers gowns
in inclusive sizing,

10:21.454 --> 10:23.056
which we
pride ourselves on,

10:23.156 --> 10:26.960
and a wide range of shades
that really pop on all skin tones.

10:27.060 --> 10:29.195
Brides and bridesmaids
can also shop

10:29.295 --> 10:30.663
from the comfort
of their home

10:30.763 --> 10:32.699
through our live
virtual consultations

10:32.799 --> 10:34.734
and our thriving
social media community.

10:34.834 --> 10:38.471
So, Sharks, now that you know
a little bit about Bridal Babes,

10:38.571 --> 10:40.173
who's ready to get...

10:40.273 --> 10:41.407
Hitched?
Hitched?

10:41.508 --> 10:43.376
Wow. So good.
Great job.

10:43.476 --> 10:44.511
Great job, guys.

10:44.611 --> 10:45.845
That's
a beautiful dress.

10:45.945 --> 10:47.313
Ashley, what do they cost--
They're beautiful, first of all.

10:47.413 --> 10:48.414
Thank you. Absolutely.

10:48.515 --> 10:50.817
What do they cost?
Give us an average.

10:50.917 --> 10:51.985
We have two collections.

10:52.085 --> 10:55.488
Our Classic Collection
averages $13.31,

10:55.588 --> 10:57.724
and we price them
at $44.05.

10:57.824 --> 10:59.959
Wow.
That's amazingly affordable.

11:00.059 --> 11:02.896
Sorry, how much?
You sell Ashley's dress...

11:02.996 --> 11:04.230
Well, not--
That's the Luxe Collection.

11:04.330 --> 11:05.331
This is
the Luxe Collection.

11:05.431 --> 11:06.599
Okay, how much would
Ashley's dress be?

11:06.699 --> 11:10.303
$67 landed, and we'll sell it
for about $228 on average.

11:10.403 --> 11:13.306
Hang on.
That dress is $200?

11:13.406 --> 11:15.675
It's amazing.
Isn't that really expensive
for a bridal dress?

11:15.775 --> 11:17.477
No.
So, it's actually not.

