a more high-end line.

11:22.182 --> 11:25.251
And our goal really is
to provide as much diversity

11:25.351 --> 11:27.654
in the product type,
because we want to service

11:27.754 --> 11:30.456
an audience that has been
overlooked for years.

11:30.557 --> 11:34.994
I mean, guys, you are speaking
my language 100% and entirely.

11:35.094 --> 11:39.566
Like, the whole inclusive
thing is a huge gap in the market.

11:39.666 --> 11:41.234
I really just want to
understand, for you guys,

11:41.334 --> 11:42.502
like, what is inclusive?

11:42.602 --> 11:44.537
Like, what are you
actually selling? What sizes?

11:44.637 --> 11:48.107
Inclusive sizing
is sizes 2 through 26,

11:48.208 --> 11:50.210
which are actually
ready to ship.
That's inclusive.

11:50.310 --> 11:55.582
We also have a special-order
collection in sizes 26 to 32.

11:55.682 --> 11:57.283
The greatest challenge
for every business

11:57.383 --> 12:00.086
that services weddings
is customer acquisition.

12:00.186 --> 12:02.021
How are you getting
your customer?

12:02.121 --> 12:05.225
So our core platform we're on
is Instagram.

12:05.325 --> 12:08.494
Our Instagram community
is about 90,000 followers,

12:08.595 --> 12:10.863
and we have about
60,000 on TikTok,

12:10.964 --> 12:12.699
which has just grown tremendously.

12:12.799 --> 12:14.901
We are a community.
We talk to our customers.

12:14.968 --> 12:16.569
We post three to four
times a day.

12:16.669 --> 12:18.671
But the secret sauce
to getting those customers

12:18.771 --> 12:20.240
is the fabric
you all have.

12:20.340 --> 12:21.541
Okay,
so is it this one?

12:21.641 --> 12:23.543
This is what actually changed
our business model.

12:23.643 --> 12:25.111
How can a fabric be--

12:25.211 --> 12:26.813
So, when we put
these dresses out,

12:26.913 --> 12:29.182
