That's why I invented
the Marker Parker,

21:40.800 --> 21:43.269
the perfect spot
to park your markers.

21:43.369 --> 21:44.436
Cool.
How does it work?

21:44.537 --> 21:47.706
Marker Parker
grips your marker caps tight,

21:47.807 --> 21:50.976
so you just remove
the drawing part.

21:51.076 --> 21:54.013
And when you're done with it,
you put it right back.

21:54.113 --> 21:57.183
Marker Parker's ergonomic
shape and squishy texture

21:57.283 --> 21:59.318
makes it easy
for kids to grip,

21:59.418 --> 22:01.420
and its playful design
encourages them

22:01.520 --> 22:04.089
to put their markers back
where they belong.

22:04.190 --> 22:06.959
So no more markers
rolling onto the floor.

22:07.059 --> 22:09.261
No more lost
marker caps.

22:09.361 --> 22:11.864
No more
dried-out markers.

22:11.964 --> 22:13.699
And when a marker
<i>does</i> run out of ink,

22:13.799 --> 22:17.203
