we decided to make
a little modification

23:37.950 --> 23:41.086
in order to make it fit
for fine-tip markers as well.

23:41.186 --> 23:43.589
Amy, it's an eloquent
solution. I get it.

23:43.689 --> 23:45.524
But what stops
the manufacturer,

23:45.624 --> 23:47.726
having seen this,
from doing it themselves?

23:47.826 --> 23:50.296
We filed a provisional patent
back in November.

23:50.396 --> 23:53.365
She thought of the idea
exactly one year ago, July--

23:53.465 --> 23:54.667
Oh,
Marlo thought of the idea.

23:54.767 --> 23:57.202
Oh, I'm so sorry!
Yeah, she invented this.

23:57.303 --> 23:58.370
- Aww.
- Oh, I had no idea.

23:58.470 --> 23:59.405
I just helped her take it
to the finish line.

23:59.505 --> 24:00.572
And what do
you sell it for?

24:00.673 --> 24:03.075
What's the price?
$15.

24:03.175 --> 24:04.276
-$15.
- Wow.

24:04.376 --> 24:06.845
You do? And what does
it cost you to make this?

24:06.946 --> 24:07.980
$2.71, landed.

24:08.080 --> 24:09.148
- Wow.
- Nice.

24:09.248 --> 24:10.449
- Wow. Great margin.
- That's really great.

24:10.549 --> 24:12.117
Yeah!
So, Amy,

24:12.217 --> 24:13.585
how are you selling these
at the moment?

24:13.686 --> 24:14.820
How are you marketing them?

24:14.920 --> 24:18.557
So, Big Bee, Little Bee is
the business that we started

24:18.657 --> 24:21.527
about six years ago,
and it just started with

24:21.627 --> 24:25.130
a-a towel that I invented
for her as a baby.

24:25.230 --> 24:27.132
Do you want to share
some of our-- our products?

24:27.232 --> 24:29.368
Sure.
This is the ScrubBEE.

24:29.468 --> 24:32.304
It helps kids learn
to wash themselves.

24:32.404 --> 24:35.341
It's not a sponge,
so germs don't collect on it,

24:35.441 --> 24:38.944
and it has a solid handle
and soft bristles.

24:39.044 --> 24:42.781
Oh, great idea. Marlo,
and do you make the straw too?

24:42.881 --> 24:44.516
So, that-- that's
the Build-A-Straw.

24:44.616 --> 24:46.585
That becomes
a full-size straw.

24:46.685 --> 24:47.786
Ohh.

24:47.886 --> 24:49.054
It's completely unique
in that--

24:49.154 --> 24:51.290
and so when you take it apart,
it's super easy to clean.

24:51.390 --> 24:53.592
So, Amy, obviously, you have a
lot of products in the company.

24:53.692 --> 24:54.960
Like, what's your
hero product?

24:55.060 --> 24:56.895
What are you selling, and
how much of it are you
selling?

24:56.996 --> 24:58.731
Okay, so,
our hero product

24:58.831 --> 25:00.933
has been
that little silicone scrubber.

25:01.033 --> 25:06.739
So, last year, we did
$230,000 worth of sales.

25:06.839 --> 25:07.740
Of the scrubber?

25:07.840 --> 25:09.274
You know,
of the whole business.

25:09.375 --> 25:10.275
Of everything.

25:10.376 --> 25:12.244
But the scrubber was,
you know--

25:12.344 --> 25:13.278
is our main product.

25:13.379 --> 25:15.581
Of what percentage?
And that's with--

25:15.681 --> 25:16.682
Like 80%.

25:16.782 --> 25:17.783
Oh, wow.
Yeah, but...

25:17.883 --> 25:19.084
Wow.

25:19.184 --> 25:21.620
...that's with losing all
inventory in the second half.

25:21.720 --> 25:27.893
It has been unbelievably
difficult with quality issues,

25:27.993 --> 25:29.995
manufacturing,
supply chain.

25:30.095 --> 25:32.431
On your sales last year,
did you make a profit

25:32.531 --> 25:33.866
or did you lose money?

25:33.966 --> 25:40.339
So, we-- we grossed $97,000,
and we were profitable $2,200.

25:40.439 --> 25:41.707
Whoo!
Aww!

25:41.807 --> 25:45.277
So not only did we survive,
but we made two grand.

25:45.377 --> 25:46.612
Please don't ask me
about this year.

25:46.712 --> 25:47.980
What-- What about this year?
Ohh...

25:48.080 --> 25:49.348
Please don't ask me.
Oh, no.

25:49.448 --> 25:50.382
Please tell us.
I'm kidding.

25:50.482 --> 25:52.151
I will address--
I will address that.

25:52.251 --> 25:54.787
So, this year to date,
$110,000.

25:54.887 --> 25:56.822
We did not have ScrubBEEs
in the first half.

25:56.922 --> 25:59.925
Are you making any money
on that $110,000?

26:00.025 --> 26:01.593
No, I have lost
a fortune this year.

26:01.693 --> 26:05.197
So, right now, I'm down
$77,000, and here's why--

26:05.297 --> 26:06.932
$77,000?
Here's why.

26:07.032 --> 26:10.369
Oh. Sorry.
When my daughter came to me
with this product idea

26:10.469 --> 26:13.639
this time last year,
this was not in the pipeline.

26:13.739 --> 26:15.774
We have another product
back here that already was.

26:15.874 --> 26:17.976
The train was moving
on that product.

26:18.077 --> 26:23.382
But I was
raised by parents who...

26:23.482 --> 26:24.650
"Reach for the stars.

26:24.750 --> 26:25.884
Follow your dreams."

26:25.984 --> 26:28.620
Providing me
with every resource

26:28.720 --> 26:30.689
they could possibly
pull together

26:30.789 --> 26:32.124
to-- to help me invent,

26:32.224 --> 26:33.225
'cause that's
what I loved.

26:33.325 --> 26:35.127
I had a fear of numbers,
and it stopped me

26:35.227 --> 26:38.230
from starting a business
for a very long time.

26:38.330 --> 26:42.000
But they supported me,
and so I support her.

26:42.101 --> 26:44.103
And when she had this idea,
I asked her, I said,

26:44.203 --> 26:45.237
"This is brilliant.

26:45.337 --> 26:47.439
Do you want to make this
for other children?"

26:47.539 --> 26:50.776
When she said, "Yes,"

26:50.876 --> 26:51.977
I found the money.

26:52.077 --> 26:56.148
I've invested, so far,
$100,000 of my own money.

26:56.248 --> 26:58.584
If you ask me
in two weeks from now,

26:58.684 --> 27:01.220
I'll tell you I invested
$166,000 of my own money.

27:01.320 --> 27:03.689
Wow. Wow.
O'Leary: So, Amy and Marlo,

27:03.789 --> 27:05.491
let me just say that,
you know,

27:05.591 --> 27:07.126
we don't get many
7-year-olds in here holding--

27:07.226 --> 27:08.660
7 1/2!

27:08.760 --> 27:10.262
- 7 1/2.
- 7 1/2, Kevin.

27:10.362 --> 27:12.197
That's very impressive.
Very impressive.
You did a great job.

27:12.297 --> 27:15.767
And, Amy, um, wonderful that
you're supporting your daughter

27:15.868 --> 27:17.503
towards a journey
of entrepreneurship.

27:17.603 --> 27:18.804
That's great.

27:18.904 --> 27:21.039
However, telling me
you have fear of numbers--

27:21.140 --> 27:22.474
that's not a good story.

27:22.574 --> 27:24.409
I know.
As an investor,
what I look for

27:24.510 --> 27:26.512
is an opportunity
to take my capital

27:26.612 --> 27:29.181
and pour it on
a working business model.

27:29.281 --> 27:31.016
It's like pouring
gasoline on a fire,

27:31.116 --> 27:33.619
and I get my returns
because I accelerate

27:33.719 --> 27:35.988
by helping that company grow
and acquire customers

27:36.088 --> 27:38.090
and all the other things
that a Shark does.

27:38.190 --> 27:40.993
This has a lot of problems
in it right now.

27:41.093 --> 27:42.895
May I challenge you
for a second, please?

27:42.995 --> 27:44.730
Well, I want to get
to a place here.

27:44.830 --> 27:46.265
Sure, sorry.

27:46.365 --> 27:47.432
I'm out.

27:49.401 --> 27:52.070
I think you're going to want
to take that back.

27:52.171 --> 27:53.939
Well, let's see.

27:54.039 --> 27:55.107
This is what's next.

27:55.207 --> 27:56.975
This is
the food container.

27:57.075 --> 27:58.911
Food?
For, like, a sandwich?

27:59.011 --> 28:00.345
Food, yes. Yeah. Yeah.

28:00.445 --> 28:03.549
And it could fit
a whole apple in there.

28:03.649 --> 28:06.785
So are they-- are they
silicone sandwich storage,

28:06.885 --> 28:08.387
individual, like, self...?
Yeah.

28:08.487 --> 28:09.388
Yeah, so basically--

28:09.488 --> 28:10.622
Guys, let me jump in
real quick here.

28:10.722 --> 28:11.490
Oh.

28:11.590 --> 28:12.858
Look, one of
the great traits

28:12.958 --> 28:14.960
of any good entrepreneur
is resilience,

28:15.060 --> 28:16.662
and you certainly
have shown that.

28:16.762 --> 28:20.499
But you also have
inventor-itis, right?

28:20.599 --> 28:22.367
Which is one of
the worst traits

28:22.467 --> 28:26.872
an entrepreneur can have,
because you lost $77,000.

28:26.972 --> 28:29.541
You've got to solve the
problems that are in front of
you first.

28:29.641 --> 28:31.043
If you would have
come in and said,

28:31.143 --> 28:32.578
"The marker,
we're shipping it.

28:32.678 --> 28:34.146
We've got these sales."
We are. We do.

28:34.246 --> 28:35.547
"We've got-- We've got
cash in the bank."

28:35.647 --> 28:36.982
It's going
in Buybuy Baby.

28:37.082 --> 28:38.383
Just 'cause it's
in Buybuy Baby--

28:38.483 --> 28:40.152
You would be telling us
the numbers, right?

28:40.252 --> 28:42.588
I'll tell you the numbers.
$8,500 in sales.

28:42.688 --> 28:44.256
How many units
have we sold?

28:44.356 --> 28:46.225
Over a thousand.

28:47.426 --> 28:48.393
Over a thousand
in three-and-a-half--

28:48.493 --> 28:49.995
Okay. Amy, I'm out.
I'm out. Sorry.

28:50.095 --> 28:51.830
Okay.

28:51.930 --> 28:53.265
Amy, are you
doing this alone?

28:53.365 --> 28:54.866
No.

28:54.967 --> 28:56.301
Oh, well, of course.

28:56.401 --> 28:58.837
Of course. Of course.
She's my light.

28:58.937 --> 29:00.272
But-- But, yes.

29:00.372 --> 29:04.810
I completely love
you're teaching your daughter

29:04.910 --> 29:06.144
how to think big

29:06.245 --> 29:08.614
and how to be creative
and inventive.

29:08.714 --> 29:11.383
At the same time,
when you come up with an idea,

29:11.483 --> 29:12.951
you perfect it.

29:13.051 --> 29:15.454
You make that one product
a huge success,

29:15.554 --> 29:17.522
and then you go to the next.

29:17.623 --> 29:18.790
So, I think you just have

29:18.890 --> 29:21.460
overextended yourself
in every way.

29:21.560 --> 29:24.229
I'm so sorry.
I'm out.

29:24.329 --> 29:26.265
It's okay.
Thank you, Lori.

29:26.365 --> 29:29.901
Guys, I-I really-- So, I
really admire what you've
done.

29:30.002 --> 29:31.970
And I think just seeing
the two of you stand here

29:32.070 --> 29:35.674
as a mother and daughter,
it's just, like, amazing.

29:35.774 --> 29:37.442
You know,
it warms the heart.

29:37.542 --> 29:39.044
I do think that
you've probably

29:39.144 --> 29:40.612
overextended yourself
a little bit.

29:40.712 --> 29:43.015
There's so many products
in this brand

29:43.115 --> 29:46.385
that I don't quite understand
what you stand for, right?

29:46.485 --> 29:48.153
And I do think
there's an element

29:48.253 --> 29:52.224
of having a hero product,
really, really perfecting that,

29:52.324 --> 29:54.593
and then thinking about
other things.

29:54.693 --> 29:56.161
At the moment,
the approach just feels

29:56.261 --> 29:57.496
a little bit scatterbrained.

29:57.596 --> 30:00.966
And while this might be
an amazing business for you two,

30:01.066 --> 30:02.801
I just don't think it's
something that I can invest in.

30:02.901 --> 30:04.836
So for those reasons,
I'm out.

30:07.472 --> 30:08.874
Thank you
for your time.

30:08.974 --> 30:12.444
Oh, you're so welcome.
You're so welcome. Aww.

30:12.544 --> 30:16.715
Marlo, I have 4-year-old
twins, and they love to draw.

30:16.815 --> 30:19.818
They would love
something like this.

30:19.918 --> 30:24.189
And I know you can't see it,
but I have bees on my suit.

30:24.289 --> 30:27.526
And so I love the bees.
I love bees.

30:27.626 --> 30:31.496
Amy, I was going
to make you an offer,

30:31.596 --> 30:34.733
until you started
showing us more product.

30:34.833 --> 30:37.736
I think, you know,
when you're really small,

30:37.836 --> 30:40.806
you have to be laser focused,
and I kind of feel that

30:40.906 --> 30:44.176
your real strength and value
is inventing.

30:44.276 --> 30:48.413
So perhaps you look at us
as a design studio

30:48.513 --> 30:49.648
and license
these products.

30:49.748 --> 30:53.352
Amy, I-I think you are
phenomenal at design.

30:53.452 --> 30:55.520
That's a really
good way to look at it.

30:55.620 --> 30:58.090
But if you're a design studio,
you need somebody to sell it.

30:58.190 --> 30:59.958
I'm not so much
a license guy.

31:00.058 --> 31:02.794
I want to help build
the business around this.

31:02.894 --> 31:06.365
I mean, I wish you all the
best, but for the business investment,

31:06.465 --> 31:09.134
I'm sorry, I'm out.

31:09.234 --> 31:11.069
Okay. Thank you.
Thank you.

31:11.169 --> 31:12.371
- Good luck, guys.
- Good luck, guys.

31:12.471 --> 31:13.372
Good luck, guys.

31:13.472 --> 31:14.272
Keep on doing
what you do.

31:14.373 --> 31:15.173
Thank you, guys.

31:15.273 --> 31:16.608
Good job, Marlo.
You were amazing.

31:16.708 --> 31:18.944
Good job, Marlo.
You were amazing.

31:19.044 --> 31:22.547
I'm happy that Mama
got what she wanted.

31:22.647 --> 31:25.384
She like-- She always wanted
to go on "Shark Tank,"

31:25.484 --> 31:28.520
and she's on
"Shark Tank" now.

31:28.620 --> 31:31.556
I did get what I wanted, honey.

31:31.656 --> 31:33.658
Well, Robert, I think
you did a great job

31:33.759 --> 31:35.327
of crushing
Marlo's dreams.

31:35.427 --> 31:36.995
No kidding. "I was
going to make you an offer..."

31:37.095 --> 31:38.463
7 1/2 years old.
Oh, my God.

31:38.563 --> 31:39.564
She's decimated.
I mean--

31:39.664 --> 31:41.266
Well, I was.
I was!

31:41.366 --> 31:42.501
Well, then do it!

31:42.601 --> 31:45.937
It broke my heart, what you
did. I wept like a baby.

31:58.250 --> 31:59.751
Next up is a company

31:59.851 --> 32:02.721
that combines luxury
with the great outdoors.

32:12.030 --> 32:13.532
Hi, Sharks.

32:13.632 --> 32:17.936
My name is Tracy Slocum,
and I'm from Albany, New York.

32:18.036 --> 32:21.706
I'm the CEO and founder
of Pretty Rugged.

32:21.807 --> 32:26.812
Today I'm seeking $200,000
for 10% of my company.

32:26.912 --> 32:30.615
Sharks,
my great-great-grandfather

32:30.715 --> 32:34.052
was the first man
to sail alone around the world.

32:34.152 --> 32:35.821
His name was
Captain Joshua Slocum.

32:35.921 --> 32:36.988
I'm Tracy Slocum.

32:37.088 --> 32:38.323
Wow.
That's pretty cool.

32:38.423 --> 32:40.492
He was a pioneer of his time,

32:40.592 --> 32:44.696
and his trailblazing spirit
is sewn into everything I do.

32:44.796 --> 32:49.100
So, Sharks, I made a blanket
that is waterproof and windproof

32:49.201 --> 32:52.537
on one side,
and faux fur on the other.

32:52.637 --> 32:55.574
You can see that this is
the faux-fur side,

32:55.674 --> 32:58.310
and this is the waterproof
and windproof side.

32:58.410 --> 33:01.112
And that's when
Pretty Rugged was born.

33:01.213 --> 33:03.014
But I didn't just
stop there, Sharks.

33:03.114 --> 33:06.318
I created an entire
lifestyle brand

33:06.418 --> 33:08.720
around luxury and function,

33:08.820 --> 33:14.226
making products that were made
for life, luxury redefined.

33:14.326 --> 33:17.062
So, Sharks, who wants to jump
on this ride with me

33:17.162 --> 33:19.097
and take this around the world

33:19.197 --> 33:21.533
just like
my great-great-grandfather
did?

33:21.633 --> 33:23.101
Wow.
Wow.

33:23.201 --> 33:25.036
That's pretty cool
that he went around the world.

33:25.136 --> 33:27.973
Yeah, he was 51 years old
when he did it.

33:28.073 --> 33:30.108
He had lost the love
of his life. Aw.

33:30.208 --> 33:31.810
He was given a boat.

33:31.910 --> 33:35.580
He rebuilt that boat
in about 13 months. Wow.

33:35.680 --> 33:39.117
And while he rebuilt it,
he rebuilt himself.

33:39.217 --> 33:43.088
And he had a goal
that was so big,

33:43.188 --> 33:44.656
and people really doubted him.

33:44.756 --> 33:49.928
And I can really relate to
this heritage and this DNA myself.

33:50.028 --> 33:52.964
I started Pretty Rugged
when I was 43 years old.

33:53.064 --> 33:54.399
And how long ago was that,
Tracy?

33:54.499 --> 33:56.401
That was in 2017.

33:56.501 --> 33:57.769
Do you want to tell us
what these are?

33:57.869 --> 33:58.870
Can we open these?

33:58.970 --> 34:01.339
Yes, would you please
open your gifts?

34:01.439 --> 34:02.741
Oh, wow.

34:02.841 --> 34:04.209
These are very nice, Tracy.

34:04.309 --> 34:05.277
Beautiful.

34:05.377 --> 34:06.878
My original
faux-fur blankets.

34:06.978 --> 34:09.247
They're meant to feel
like real sheared mink.
They do.

34:09.347 --> 34:13.084
And the backing's waterproof,
so the fur goes around you,

34:13.184 --> 34:15.587
and you sit on a waterproof,
like a-a--

34:15.687 --> 34:16.755
I have it backwards.

34:16.855 --> 34:17.756
You do.

34:17.856 --> 34:18.723
Come on, Robert.
Sort it out.

34:18.823 --> 34:19.958
This is how it works, Robert.

34:20.058 --> 34:21.860
Look at you.

34:21.960 --> 34:23.595
Never mind me,
I'm gonna take a snooze

34:23.695 --> 34:24.629
during your presentation.

34:24.729 --> 34:26.064
Okay, I know.
I hope not.

34:26.164 --> 34:27.432
But this is the real me.

34:27.532 --> 34:31.336
So, picture being outside,
and you're sitting around,

34:31.436 --> 34:32.871
and you're on
either wet seats--

34:32.971 --> 34:35.173
You know how the dew makes
the seats get wet?

34:35.273 --> 34:36.541
Yeah, absolutely.
It's cold.

34:36.641 --> 34:38.143
Okay, so this is--
That looks beautiful on you.

34:38.243 --> 34:39.611
Thank you.

34:39.711 --> 34:44.516
So I created the blanket line,
and I launched in 2018.

34:44.616 --> 34:47.052
I walked into
the Jacob Javits Center,

34:47.152 --> 34:50.255
and it was a huge
New York Now show.

34:50.355 --> 34:53.024
I had never been
to a trade show in my life.

34:53.124 --> 34:56.194
I walked in with paper walls
and a pallet table

34:56.294 --> 34:57.696
that I made myself,

34:57.796 --> 35:02.500
and I left there winning Best
New Product and Best in Market.

35:02.601 --> 35:03.602
- Wow.
- Wow.

35:03.702 --> 35:05.503
And I was awarded,
in my first year,

35:05.604 --> 35:07.005
one of
Oprah's Favorite Things.

35:07.105 --> 35:09.240
Wow!
I had instant credibility.

35:09.341 --> 35:12.344
After I won my awards
at the New York Now,

35:12.444 --> 35:16.214
my husband's business had
a complete loss from a flood.

35:16.314 --> 35:18.416
Oh, no.
And we-- we lost everything.

35:18.516 --> 35:20.585
And Pretty Rugged,
very similar to

35:20.685 --> 35:24.556
when I was talking about
Joshua, kind of rebuilt me as
a person.

35:24.656 --> 35:28.860
And this-- this has been my
journey, and this is my passion,

35:28.960 --> 35:33.898
and that's why it's so
important to me that I do this.

35:33.999 --> 35:38.570
I-I can do this. I need-- I-I
want a strategic partner here.

35:38.670 --> 35:41.573
I want someone who gets this
and understands

35:41.673 --> 35:44.075
and wants to help me
take this to the next level.

35:44.175 --> 35:45.076
How much is
this blanket?

35:45.176 --> 35:46.645
That's $290.

35:46.745 --> 35:48.380
How much is what
Emma was wearing?

35:48.480 --> 35:50.048
That's $220.

35:50.148 --> 35:52.350
So, what does it cost you
to manufacture the blanket,

35:52.450 --> 35:54.386
and then the thing
that I was wearing, the cape?

35:54.486 --> 35:57.822
The blankets cost me
about $36 to $40.

35:57.922 --> 35:58.657
- Wow!
- Whoa!

35:58.757 --> 35:59.658
My margins are huge.

35:59.758 --> 36:00.892
Good margins!
Margin on fire!

36:00.992 --> 36:04.562
My retail margins
hover around 80%.
Whoo-hoo!

36:04.663 --> 36:07.766
Oh, my God!
And my wholesale margins
are 70%.

36:07.866 --> 36:10.835
Oh, delicious.
And I've sold over 30,000 units.

36:10.935 --> 36:13.838
My lifetime sales
are just shy of $3 million.

36:13.938 --> 36:14.906
Wow.

36:15.006 --> 36:16.274
What were your sales
last year?

36:16.374 --> 36:19.344
Yes, last year,
I did $1.197 million.

36:19.444 --> 36:20.779
And what did you
make on that?

36:20.879 --> 36:23.181
I netted $32,000.

36:23.281 --> 36:24.716
What?

36:24.816 --> 36:29.954
If you made 80% margins,
why did you only net $32,000

36:30.055 --> 36:31.956
on $1 million?
Trade shows.

36:32.057 --> 36:33.992
We-- We had another
purchase order last year

36:34.092 --> 36:35.760
that came in
late in the year.

36:35.860 --> 36:37.595
How much did you spend
on trade shows?

36:37.696 --> 36:41.866
Last year, we spent about
$180,000 on trade shows.

36:41.966 --> 36:42.901
Wow.
There we go. Okay.

36:42.967 --> 36:44.035
A lot of trade shows
this year.

36:44.135 --> 36:45.904
I'm doing
20 trade shows this year.

36:46.004 --> 36:47.038
Oh, wow.

36:47.138 --> 36:49.140
Supply-chain issues
have been an issue.

36:49.240 --> 36:53.745
Last year, I ran out of
product, so I made a strategic decision

36:53.845 --> 36:56.981
to make a big purchase order
of about $400,000

36:57.082 --> 36:58.850
that came in
just a couple weeks ago.

36:58.950 --> 37:03.788
Duties-- I-I get knocked 25%
on tariffs from China.

37:03.888 --> 37:06.591
My-- My ad spend
was $68,000.

37:06.691 --> 37:08.093
O'Leary:
I'm listening to your numbers.

37:08.193 --> 37:10.061
It's like you said
just a few moments ago,

37:10.161 --> 37:11.196
you're running around
the country,

37:11.296 --> 37:13.698
spending 20% of revenue
at trade shows.

37:13.798 --> 37:15.633
It's working.
You're selling over $1
million.

37:15.734 --> 37:16.901
That's amazing.

37:17.001 --> 37:20.171
But I'm looking at it as
an investor, saying to myself,

37:20.271 --> 37:22.540
"There's not
any room for me."

37:22.640 --> 37:24.476
I mean,
I give you $200,000 for 10%.

37:24.576 --> 37:28.346
That's a $2 million valuation.
It's not worth $2 million yet.

37:28.446 --> 37:29.881
Could be one day.

37:29.981 --> 37:33.818
But for me, it's just, how do
I pour gasoline on this fire?

37:33.918 --> 37:35.587
Because that's what I do
in my investments.

37:35.687 --> 37:38.757
I-I find a model that's
working, and you need cash,

37:38.857 --> 37:41.259
I have cash,
I give you cash,

37:41.359 --> 37:43.795
you pour it on the business,
we make more cash.

37:43.895 --> 37:46.097
Everybody's happy.
Cash, cash, cash.

37:46.197 --> 37:48.066
And-- But I don't see that
here, Tracy. I'm sorry.

37:48.166 --> 37:50.168
I think you're fantastic,
but I'm out.

37:50.268 --> 37:52.470
Thank you.
I appreciate that.

37:52.570 --> 37:54.706
Tracy, I'm-- I'm going
to tell you right now,

37:54.806 --> 37:56.307
I actually
really admire you.

37:56.407 --> 37:58.443
I admire the fact that,
at this point in your life,

37:58.543 --> 38:01.646
you've decided to just take
a chance and do something else.

38:01.746 --> 38:03.648
I'll tell you right now,
I touched this product.

38:03.748 --> 38:05.884
I put it on,
and it feels great.

38:06.017 --> 38:08.486
For me,
working in fashion right now,

38:08.586 --> 38:10.655
it doesn't feel right
to invest in something--

38:10.755 --> 38:12.590
Even though this is not
real fur,

38:12.690 --> 38:14.526
I think we're seeing
a real downtrend

38:14.626 --> 38:16.761
in the trend overall
of fur,

38:16.861 --> 38:18.396
and certainly,
the younger generation

38:18.496 --> 38:19.831
don't want anything
to do with it.

38:19.931 --> 38:24.435
So for that reason,
I'm out.

38:24.536 --> 38:26.304
Tracy, I think
you're going to do great.

38:26.404 --> 38:27.839
I think it's
a great product.
Thank you.

38:27.939 --> 38:29.808
But I'm just not sure
how I can help you.

38:29.908 --> 38:32.110
So for those reasons,
I'm out.

38:32.210 --> 38:34.479
Thank you, Mark.
I appreciate that.

38:34.579 --> 38:36.181
Lori? Robert?

38:49.894 --> 38:51.329
Three Sharks are out.

38:51.429 --> 38:54.332
Lori and Robert are Tracy's
last chance for a deal

38:54.432 --> 38:58.069
for her luxury outdoor
accessory business, Pretty Rugged.

38:58.169 --> 38:59.737
So, what are
this year's sales,

38:59.838 --> 39:01.639
and what is the profit
so far on that?

39:01.739 --> 39:04.442
So right now, my booked sales-- my gross sales,

39:04.542 --> 39:07.445
not my preorders,
are $715,000, okay?

39:07.545 --> 39:09.047
So far.
So far.

39:09.147 --> 39:13.117
According to my P&L,
I'm at negative $250,000.

39:13.218 --> 39:14.652
Ooh! Explain.
Wow.

39:14.752 --> 39:17.822
My trade shows-- I did four
trade shows last year.

39:17.922 --> 39:20.692
I'm doing like almost
20 of them this year,

39:20.792 --> 39:22.160
so it's-- it's a lot.

39:22.260 --> 39:25.296
So trade shows can be 5 grand
a show, they can be 10. Yeah.

39:25.396 --> 39:26.397
Or they can be 200.

39:26.497 --> 39:27.966
They can be-- You know,
what are they costing?

39:28.066 --> 39:30.268
So, most of them hover between
$15,000 and $30,000.

39:30.368 --> 39:32.737
So, talk to us about
the last year.
Tracy, is it just you?
Do you have any staff?

39:32.837 --> 39:35.607
Okay, so this is
run by five women.

39:35.707 --> 39:37.909
We are
a women-owned company.

39:38.009 --> 39:40.545
It makes no sense.
It's not a viable business.

39:40.645 --> 39:41.846
Something isn't
stacking up.

39:41.946 --> 39:43.014
The inefficiencies
are crazy,

39:43.114 --> 39:44.916
'cause your margins
are what they are,

39:45.016 --> 39:46.517
and even your wholesale margin
is good.

39:46.618 --> 39:49.053
I know. That's why I'm here. I
need a person that can help me.

39:49.153 --> 39:50.588
I know I'm not doing
everything right.

39:50.688 --> 39:51.789
I'm not saying I am.

39:51.890 --> 39:54.859
Can I learn and know?
Yes, I can.

39:54.959 --> 39:58.863
I'm so good at-- at-- at
selling this product.

39:58.963 --> 40:00.865
Tracy, we just think
you need some help.

40:00.965 --> 40:03.735
I <i>do</i> need help.
Yeah, Tracy, I care-- I care less about the past.

40:03.835 --> 40:06.271
I mean, we all make mistakes.
I wasn't a financial guy.

40:06.371 --> 40:08.640
It took me three days
to do my first spreadsheet.

40:08.740 --> 40:11.576
I mean, y-yes,
you should know that better,

40:11.676 --> 40:13.878
but I think I can
help you figure that out,

40:13.978 --> 40:16.314
and I think there are people
that can figure it out.

40:16.414 --> 40:17.782
You're
an absolute winner.

40:17.882 --> 40:21.519
Like, you are
an absolute winner.

40:21.619 --> 40:23.354
All the poo-poo
that's happened in life,

40:23.454 --> 40:25.890
and you've recovered,
you've kept going.

40:25.990 --> 40:27.392
I mean,
that's what I look for.

40:27.492 --> 40:29.594
Thank you.
I couldn't
love you more.

40:29.694 --> 40:32.297
I want to be
involved with it. Okay.

40:32.397 --> 40:34.832
You know, I'm sitting here
feeling this,

40:34.933 --> 40:36.901
and really beautiful.

40:37.001 --> 40:39.237
You would not know
this isn't mink.
That's right.

40:39.337 --> 40:42.173
I mean, It's just-- I
actually like it way better,
frankly... Yeah.

40:42.273 --> 40:45.777
...because I'm a believer
in faux fur versus real fur.

40:45.877 --> 40:47.011
Yes.
Yes, me too.

40:47.111 --> 40:50.548
And then the inside is just
absolutely gorgeous, too.

40:50.648 --> 40:53.685
Your margins
are fantastic.

40:53.785 --> 40:57.121
You obviously have done
a great job of sourcing.

40:57.221 --> 41:00.558
Yes.
Robert and I both love you
and love the product.

41:00.658 --> 41:03.928
So we thought, you know what,
he can help you

41:04.028 --> 41:06.431
with the financial end of it,
and I can help you

41:06.531 --> 41:08.833
with the sales and marketing
end of it,

41:08.933 --> 41:10.768
and we would make
a good team here.

41:10.868 --> 41:12.403
What's the offer,
before the mink dies?

41:12.503 --> 41:13.571
We are gonna
offer you...

41:13.671 --> 41:15.239
$200,000...

41:15.340 --> 41:17.141
For 25%.

41:17.241 --> 41:19.877
Because we think we add
a lot of value to it, Tracy,

41:19.978 --> 41:21.446
and I think this is
one of those businesses,

41:21.546 --> 41:25.516
you got to go quick--
$200,000, 25%.

41:25.616 --> 41:27.986
Lori and I would love to be
in business with you.

41:28.086 --> 41:28.987
What do you think,
Tracy?

41:29.087 --> 41:31.322
So I'm just going to ask you,

41:31.422 --> 41:34.959
would you ever
consider 20%, not 25%?

41:35.059 --> 41:37.261
No. Tracy, we feel pretty good
about that offer.

41:37.362 --> 41:38.963
Come on.
We're gonna blow this up.

41:39.063 --> 41:40.732
We're gonna blow it up?
We're gonna blow it up!

41:40.832 --> 41:43.401
Alright. You got a deal!

41:43.501 --> 41:44.702
Boom!

41:44.802 --> 41:46.337
Whoo!

41:46.437 --> 41:47.739
Oh, well done, Tracy.

41:47.839 --> 41:50.675
I love it!
I couldn't love it more.

41:50.775 --> 41:54.045
I love it, too.
Wow. It's beautiful.

41:54.145 --> 41:55.480
Congratulations,
Tracy.

41:55.580 --> 41:57.048
Thank you so much.

41:57.148 --> 41:58.449
Okay.

41:58.549 --> 42:01.252
Yes! Oh!

42:01.352 --> 42:04.222
This is the American dream.
This is what I came here for.

42:04.322 --> 42:08.192
I thought that I would get
a Shark, but to get two Sharks,

42:08.292 --> 42:12.597
and to have them see me,
what I really feel,

42:12.697 --> 42:16.968
and-- and love the product
was everything.

42:17.068 --> 42:19.070
You know what another
great thing about this is?

42:19.170 --> 42:22.006
If you have things that you
want to hide from the public--

42:22.106 --> 42:24.776
Ohh!
You can just cover them!

42:24.876 --> 42:25.877
And they look better.
